cs.GT, cs.EC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper deals with fair allocation of public resources in participatory decision making, which involves game theory, mechanism design, and computational aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design), followed by cs.EC (Economics and Computation) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves computational social choice (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY) aspects, which are less central but still relevant.
